==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magnetize
<hw>Mag"net*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Magnetized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>prep. &
adv.</pos> <conjf>Magnetizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>magn⟦eacute⟧tiser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To communicate
magnetic properties to; to make magnetic; <as>as, to <ex>magnetize</ex>
a needle</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To attract as a magnet attracts, or like a magnet;
to move; to influence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fascinated, <qex>magnetized</qex>, as it were, by his
character.</q> <rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To bring under the influence of animal
magnetism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnetizee</ent>⟦br⟧
